{"key":"processedPost-7459006","value":{"id":7459006,"first":7458114,"last":7460218,"when":1190897058,"utime":"09/27/07 03:44 PM","content":"If CO2 was heavier enough than air that it settled to the bottom, we'd all be dead from CO2 poisoning on the surface of the planet.  CO2 mixes with the air.  To get rid of it, you exchange the air in the terrarium.  You can't simply drill a hole in the bottom and expect it to run out like water.  CO2 is found high in the atmosphere, not just at the surface.  It's the same in your terrarium.  In a completely airtight container, the CO2 would sink to the bottom.  Such is not the case with our growing containers.<br />RR","title":"Re: co2 and air."}}